<p>This is an online portal giving a summary of updates for <a href="https://vipulnaik.com">Vipul Naik</a>. The portal code and underlying personal data are in the <a href="https://github.com/vipulnaik/daily-updates">daily-updates GitHub repository</a>. Work-related updates are in a private repository restricted to the workplace; therefore links to work-related updates will only work correctly for co-workers.</p>

<p>Conventions: Dates are in my local timezone, which is Pacific Time for the entire period except the period of Sunday 2024-02-18 to Friday 2024-03-15 (both ends inclusive) when I was in India (for that period I use Indian Standard Time (IST)). Until Friday 2024-02-16 and starting Saturday 2024-03-16, I use Pacific Time. Saturday 2024-02-17 is an effectively missed date due to travel.</p>

<p>However, if I stay up past midnight on a given day, the time spent is included in the "previous day"; for instance, if I stay up past midnight from 2023-12-01 to 2023-12-02, and spend 30 minutes between 1 AM and 1:30 AM on 2023-12-02 before going to sleep, I count that time under 2023-12-01. Note, however, that screen minutes per day (that I get from my computer) strictly divide days at midnight. Time spent estimates are marked "N/A" for days when I did not track time spent. Time spent estimates are generally estimates of "process time" (time spent actually actively working) rather than wall-clock time, and therefore may be lower than one might expect of wall-clock time. I do not include daily-cadence tasks and chores (such as brushing my teeth, eating, cleaning dishes after eating, daily exercise) in personal chores in daily updates issues; I also generally do not include entertainment and self-education except when I deliberately took time out for it rather than multiplexing against other chores. I skip creating a personal daily update issue on days when I do nothing that I would normally put into such an issue.</p>

